doc.previous: Aisles are distinguished from corridors hallways walkways footpaths pavements American English sidewalks trails paths and enclosed open areas  Aisles can also be seen in shops warehouses and factories where rather than seats they have shelving to either side In warehouses and factories aisles may consist of storage pallets and in factories aisles may separate work areas In health clubs exercise equipment is normally arranged in aisles
